    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A single-page, vertically scrolling portfolio with a fixed top navigation bar for quick access to key sections: About, Skills, Projects, and Experience. The 'About' section serves as a landing hero. 'Skills' are visualized with a radar chart for quick comparison. 'Projects' are presented in an interactive card grid, with details revealed in modals to keep the main view clean. 'Experience' is shown as a vertical timeline to visualize career progression. This structure was chosen to transform the static resume into an engaging narrative, allowing recruiters to quickly access information while also demonstrating modern frontend development skills. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Summary -> Inform -> Hero Text -> None -> Clear intro.
        - Technical Skills -> Compare/Inform -> Radar Chart (Chart.js) -> Hover Tooltips -> Provides a quick, engaging visual summary of capabilities versus a dry list.
        - Projects -> Organize/Explore -> Interactive Card Grid with Modals -> Click to view details -> Prevents information overload, allowing users to dive into specific projects they find interesting. Implemented with HTML/CSS/JS.
        - Experience/Education -> Show Change -> Vertical Timeline -> Scroll -> A more compelling way to show career progression than bullet points. Implemented with structured HTML/Tailwind.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
